The original erroneous code fails because the variable lacks initialization before use. You must assign a value to the variable before printing it. Here is the corrected main class along with three additional classes to handle value assignment concatenation and comparison tasks.

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String variable = "Hello world";
        System.out.println(variable);
    }
}
```

```java
public class ValueAssigner {
    public static String assignValue() {
        String variable = "New Value";
        return variable;
    }
}
```

```java
public class StringConcatenator {
    public static String concatenate(String variable) {
        String result = variable + " and more";
        return result;
    }
}
```

```java
public class StringComparator {
    public static boolean compare(String variable) {
        String target = "Hello world";
        return variable.equals(target);
    }
}
```
